  {
    "id": "koc2012-q056",
    "type": "mcq",
    "topic": "hardware-memory",
    "subtopic": "data-block",
    "stem": "Definition of the term Data block in record is:",
    "options": [
      {
        "label": "A",
        "text": "Largest amount of data accessed from a second storage device at a time",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "B",
        "text": "Smallest amount of data accessed from a second storage device at a time",
        "isCorrect": true
      },
      {
        "label": "C",
        "text": "One record that is read or written to a disk or a tape.",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "D",
        "text": "None of the above",
        "isCorrect": false
      }
    ],
    "answerOptionLabels": [
      "B"
    ],
    "explanation": "A data block is the smallest unit of data that can be transferred to or from secondary storage in a single access; the disk cannot read half a block. Option C is the trap: a block usually holds several records (blocking factor), so it is not one record.",
    "source": {
      "file": "KOC 2012 EXAM (2).pdf",
      "exam": "KOC",
      "tier": "gold",
      "year": 2012,
      "originalNumber": 56
    },
    "keyProvenance": "inline_bold",
    "keyVerified": true,
    "verificationLevel": "double",
    "needsReview": false,
