  {
    "id": "koc2012-q070",
    "type": "mcq",
    "topic": "number-systems",
    "subtopic": "decimal-to-binary",
    "stem": "The binary form of decimal 20 is:",
    "options": [
      {
        "label": "A",
        "text": "00010100",
        "isCorrect": true
      },
      {
        "label": "B",
        "text": "00011111",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "C",
        "text": "00010101",
        "isCorrect": false
      }
    ],
    "answerOptionLabels": [
      "A"
    ],
    "explanation": "20 = 16 + 4 = 2^4 + 2^2, so the bits at positions 4 and 2 are set: 10100, padded to 8 bits as 00010100. 00010101 is 21 (an extra 1 at position 0) and 00011111 is 31.",
    "source": {
      "file": "KOC 2012 EXAM (2).pdf",
      "exam": "KOC",
      "tier": "gold",
      "year": 2012,
      "originalNumber": 70
